178
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:35,900
Hey, over here.

179
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:36,700
Oh, coming.

180
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:43,340
Wanyue.

181
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:45,820
Yanran.

182
00:13:48,340 --> 00:13:49,300
It's been 13 years.

183
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:50,700
I'm back.

184
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,140
It's good you're back.

185
00:14:04,700 --> 00:14:05,500
It's good.

186
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:09,180
Let's go home.

187
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:10,220
Alright.

188
00:14:10,300 --> 00:14:10,660
Come.

189
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:13,900
Let's go.

190
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:21,180
I brought Yanran to see you.

191
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:23,300
Zhang Hanyi

192
00:14:23,380 --> 00:14:24,500
is buried here?

193
00:14:24,620 --> 00:14:25,300
Yes.

194
00:14:26,900 --> 00:14:27,580
But

195
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:29,380
I don't see a grave.

196
00:14:30,420 --> 00:14:31,740
He was indeed buried here.

197
00:14:32,580 --> 00:14:34,220
In the first spring after his death,

198
00:14:34,780 --> 00:14:36,620
a pear tree grew here.

199
00:14:37,260 --> 00:14:38,660
Later, it grew taller and taller.

200
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:41,020
Just as the ancients said,

201
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,180
"Now, it stands tall like a pavilion."

202
00:14:46,020 --> 00:14:47,300
You love pear blossoms,

203
00:14:47,940 --> 00:14:49,500
so a pear tree is growing here.

204
00:14:51,180 --> 00:14:52,660
Someone must've planted it.

205
00:14:56,660 --> 00:14:57,940
Hanyi planted it.

206
00:15:11,980 --> 00:15:12,780
(Wanyue,)

207
00:15:14,300 --> 00:15:16,100
